  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I completely delete all Adobe CS6 files on my Mac?",
  "response": "To **completely delete all Adobe Creative Suite 6 (CS6)** files on your Mac, follow these steps. This process ensures that not only the applications but also associated files, preferences, and caches are removed.\n\n---\n\n### **1. Uninstall Adobe CS6 Applications**\n1. Open the **Applications** folder on your Mac.\n2. Drag the following Adobe CS6 applications to the Trash:\n   - Photoshop CS6\n   - Illustrator CS6\n   - InDesign CS6\n   - Premiere Pro CS6\n   - After Effects CS6\n   - Any other CS6 apps you have installed.\n\n---\n\n### **2. Delete Adobe CS6 Support Files**\nAdobe applications leave behind support files in various locations. Here's how to remove them:\n\n#### **a. Remove Adobe Folders in the Library**\n1. Open **Finder** and go to the **Go** menu.\n2. Select **Go to Folder** and enter the following paths one by one:\n   - `/Library/Application Support/Adobe/`\n   - `/Library/Preferences/Adobe/`\n   - `/Library/Caches/Adobe/`\n3. Delete any folders or files related to CS6.\n\n#### **b. Remove User-Specific Files**\n1. Open **Finder** and go to the **Go** menu.\n2. Select **Go to Folder** and enter the following path:\n   `~/Library/`\n3. Check the following folders and delete any CS6-related files:\n   - `~/Library/Application Support/Adobe/`\n   - `~/Library/Preferences/Adobe/`\n   - `~/Library/Caches/Adobe/`\n   - `~/Library/Logs/Adobe/`\n   - `~/Library/Saved Application State/com.adobe.*` (look for CS6-related files)\n\n#### **c. Remove Adobe Extensions**\n1. Go to the **Go to Folder** path:\n   `/Library/Extensions/`\n2. Delete any Adobe-related extensions (e.g., `AdobeGraphicsManager.kext`).\n\n#### **d. Remove Adobe Fonts (Optional)**\nIf you installed Adobe fonts, delete them from:\n   `/Library/Fonts/Adobe/`\n\n---\n\n### **3. Empty Trash**\n1. Right-click on the **Trash** icon in the Dock.\n2. Select **Empty Trash** to permanently delete all Adobe CS6 files.\n\n---\n\n### **4. Optional: Use Adobe's Creative Cloud Cleaner Tool**\nIf you want to ensure all traces of Adobe CS6 are removed, download and run Adobe's **Creative Cloud Cleaner Tool**:\n1. Download it from the official Adobe website.\n2. Follow the instructions to remove leftover Adobe files.\n\n---\n\n### **5. Restart Your Mac**\nAfter completing the above steps, restart your Mac to ensure all changes take effect.\n\nBy following these steps, you\u2019ll have completely removed all Adobe CS6 files from your Mac.",
